kernel-5.15-rt-xanmod1 x86_64
Only run build-all-kernel-pkgs.sh

This kernel unlock some serious performance improvements
install this before wine-tkg

Right now the configuration is unfinished, it just the normal generic configuration.

This is still experimental and unfinished but still somewhat useful

https://xanmod.org/

Run first time to avoid conflicts with pkgs:
removepkg kernel-source kernel-generic kernel-modules kernel-headers

To install:
installpkg /tmp/output-x86_64-5.15.31-rt38-xanmod1/kernel*.txz

Initrd command:
/usr/share/mkinitrd/mkinitrd_command_generator.sh -k 5.15.31-rt38-xanmod1

You can swap out the configuration file but dont add localversion, it have not been tested

You might want to blacklist: /etc/slackpkg/blacklist

kernel-source
kernel-modules
kernel-headers
kernel-firmware
